events.name: Le Peep
events.description: If you enjoy brunches, this is the place for you. Why settle for iHop when you can go with NU CS students to get the finest French Toast in Evanston?!

events.name: Terra & Vine
events.description: Join us for some cheese and wine night (if you are of age). Dress code is formal so break out the suits and dresses.

events.name: Taco Diablo
events.description: It’s Taco Tuesday! We will be putting the infamous “Diablo Taco” to the test. Bring your taste buds for this fiery meal!

events.name: That Little Mexican Cafe
events.description: Guac fanatics assemble! Come hang with us as we check out this new Mexican food spot and get to know more freshmen on campus.

events.name: Buffalo Joe's
events.description: We’re going out for Wing Night Wednesday. All you can eat 50 cent wings with the post-grad students. Who says no to 50 cent wings? Not you!

events.name: Gigio's Pizzeria
events.description: Thin and deep dish lovers in this group. As long as you like pizza and want to meet new undergrads, come through!

events.name: Olive Mountain Grill
events.description: Join the MSA as we check out Olive Mountain for their famous gyro. Food is halal certified if that is a concern.

events.name: Giardanos
events.description: You haven’t experienced Chicago until you have Giardanos Deep Dish pizza. We’ll be meeting up with local Chicago natives at NU to enjoy this meal.

events.name: Farmhouse Evanston
events.description: IEEE group members are hosting a meal for anyone interested in joining the club. Come enjoy some local Evanston meal and learn more about IEEE!

events.name: Five & Dine
events.description: Group of transfer students craving Mediterranean. All are welcome.

events.name: Chez Benoit Bistro
events.description: Trying new cuisine and meals such as duck. Join if you would like to meet Medill and SESP students from all levels.

events.name: The Irish Mill
events.description: This event is for you guys who want to enjoy a fun night of trying different Irish Whiskey and food. Group is 21+ but anyone can join if they don’t want to drink.

events.name: Plateia Mediterranean Kitchen Bar
events.description: Event created and is being hosted by the MCC for anyone looking to learn more about the different cultures at NU. Please don’t hesitate to join. Strangers welcome!

events.name: Demetri's Greek Restaurant
events.description: If you are interested in hearing about Master’s Programs like Kellogg, come check us out and join us for a big fat Greek meal!

events.name: Peppercorns Kitchen
events.description: Just a bunch of hungry undergrads looking to try to new cuisines. All levels of graduating classes are welcomed to join.
